#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.241"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.241:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.241:0.2"
msgid "24. Kammavagga"
msgstr "24. Deeds"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.241:0.3"
msgid "241. Samaṇasutta"
msgstr "241. Ascetics"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo → bhikkhave samaṇo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.241:1.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Idheva, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo, idha dutiyo samaṇo, idha tatiyo samaṇo, "
"idha catuttho samaṇo;"
msgstr ""
"“‘Only here is there a true ascetic, here a second ascetic, here a third "
"ascetic, and here a fourth ascetic."

# Note that the reading here differs from that attributed by BB to the Burmese text, and here that reading is attributed to the Thai texts. I follow BB.
#. VAR: aññehī’ti → samaṇehi aññeti (bj, pts1, mr) | … aññehi (s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.241:1.2"
msgid "suññā parappavādā samaṇehi aññehī’ti—"
msgstr "Other sects are empty of ascetics.’"

msgctxt "an4.241:1.3"
msgid "evametaṃ, bhikkhave, sammā sīhanādaṃ nadatha."
msgstr "This, mendicants, is how you should rightly roar your lion’s roar."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo → bhikkhave samaṇo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.241:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo?"
msgstr "And who is the first ascetic?"

msgctxt "an4.241:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti "
"avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of three fetters—is a stream-enterer, "
"not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening."

msgctxt "an4.241:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo."
msgstr "This is the first ascetic."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.241:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dutiyo samaṇo?"
msgstr "And who is the second ascetic?"

msgctxt "an4.241:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ "
"tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of "
"greed, hate, and delusion—is a once-returner. They come back to this world "
"once only, then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "an4.241:3.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo samaṇo."
msgstr "This is the second ascetic."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.241:4.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, tatiyo samaṇo?"
msgstr "And who is the third ascetic?"

msgctxt "an4.241:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who—with the ending of the five lower fetters—is reborn "
"spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from "
"that world."

msgctxt "an4.241:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo samaṇo."
msgstr "This is the third ascetic."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.241:5.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, catuttho samaṇo?"
msgstr "And who is the fourth ascetic?"

msgctxt "an4.241:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an4.241:5.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho samaṇo."
msgstr "This is the fourth ascetic."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.241:6.1"
msgid ""
"‘Idheva, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇo, idha dutiyo samaṇo, idha tatiyo samaṇo, "
"idha catuttho samaṇo;"
msgstr ""
"‘Only here is there a true ascetic, here a second ascetic, here a third "
"ascetic, and here a fourth ascetic."

msgctxt "an4.241:6.2"
msgid "suññā parappavādā samaṇebhi aññehī’ti—"
msgstr "Other sects are empty of ascetics.’"

msgctxt "an4.241:6.3"
msgid "evametaṃ, bhikkhave, sammā sīhanādaṃ nadathā”ti."
msgstr "This, mendicants, is how you should rightly roar your lion’s roar.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.241:6.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
